  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Crumble the <strong>baby chestnut mushrooms&nbsp;</strong>(this saves time and creates an interesting texture)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, <span class=\"text-highlight\">wide-based</span> pan (preferably non-stick), with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil<span class=\"text-highlight\">&nbsp;</span></strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">over a high heat&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork mince</strong> and the&nbsp;<strong>crumbled mushrooms</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 8-10 min or unt<span class=\"text-highlight\">il cooked through an</span>d caramelised</p>\r\n<p>Once caramelised, wash then add the <strong>baby leaf spinach</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until wilted</p>\r\n<p>Once wilted, transfer everything to a plate (reserve the pan)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop the <strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">brown&nbsp;</span>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Strip the <strong>thyme</strong> leaves from the stems, discarding the stems,<span class=\"text-highlight\"> and chop them finely</span></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-low heat with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable&nbsp;oil</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>beef stock <span class=\"text-highlight\">cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></span></strong> in <span class=\"text-highlight\">150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span></span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">&nbsp;&ndash;</span> this is your <strong>stock&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1596.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>thyme leaves</strong> and <strong>b<span class=\"text-highlight\">ay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span>&nbsp;</span></strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>\r\n<p>Once fragrant, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms</p>\r\n<p>Add&nbsp;the <strong>stock&nbsp;</strong>gradually <span class=\"text-highlight\">and</span> whisk for 5-8 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains <span class=\"text-highlight\">&ndash;</span> this is your&nbsp;<strong>b&eacute;chamel</strong></p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, grate the<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
